      • toMap

        public Map toMap()
        Convert the command line to a map. The command line is assumed to conform to the syntax -f arg. Because we are not looking for a specific argument the syntax -farg has limited supported as we cannot tell if this is an argument name (whose value would be boolean true) or the argument f whose value is arg. The former possibility is assumed.

        Each arg value is put in a map with the key of the argument name and the value as a string. If an argument is repeated then the last one found is placed in the map. If the argument value is not a single token then only the first one specified will be available.
